con:method.name: registerUsingPOST
con:method.con:description:
This method creates a new Mobile User account with non-active status (active = false), generates a random code and sends it via SMS to confirm the user phone number submitted during registration.
Default account type is CONSUMER, but if there's any matching Contact exists in WEB Simply Connect system or if Web Access is configured at the 3rd step, then this user becomes linked to the Contact and gets PROVIDER account type. Step 1. Register new user (Sign Up as Consumer)

con:parameter.con:name: ssn
con:parameter.con:description: social security number (SSN). a numeric string with no whitespaces, hyphens, or other dividers

con:parameter.con:name: timeZoneOffset
con:parameter.con:description: Timezone Offset - the time difference between UTC time and local time, in minutes (example -120 for GMT+2)

con:parameter.con:name: signupWithoutResident
con:parameter.con:description: If set to false and no associated residents present in the system, request will throw “no.associated.patients.found” error, user will not be registered. Otherwise, user will be registered without any associated records.

con:method.name: registerFromWebUsingPOST
con:method.con:description:
This method creates a new Mobile User account with non-active status (active = false), generates a random code and sends it via SMS to confirm the user phone number added via WEB Simply Connect system during Contact creation.
If `login` matches email of any existing user, then this user becomes linked to the Web contact (no new records created in this case).
New user's account type is PROVIDER, existing user's account type may be PROVIDER or PROVIDER + CONSUMER.
The 401 - "Bad credentials" response indicates that authorization has been refused for those credentials (check `companyId` / `login` / `password` parameters and try again). Step 1. Register new user (Sign Up via "I already have an account in Web S.C.")

con:parameter.con:name: companyId
con:parameter.con:description: company id (e.g. RBA), max length = 10 characters, CAN NOT contain slash character (`/`)

con:parameter.con:name: login
con:parameter.con:description: login (usually it's email, but in general it can be any string), CAN NOT contain slash character (`/`), max length 150

con:parameter.con:name: password
con:parameter.con:description: password used for web authentication, min length = 8 characters, max length = 255 characters

con:parameter.con:name: timeZoneOffset
con:parameter.con:description: Timezone Offset - the time difference between UTC time and local time, in minutes (example -120 for GMT+2)

con:method.name: registerProviderUsingPOST
con:method.con:description:
This method creates a new Mobile User account with non-active status (active = false) and account type of PROVIDER, generates a random code and sends it via SMS to confirm the user phone number submitted during registration.
The registered user (if approved) will have access to WEB Simply Connect system and will be searchable in Physicians list. Step 1. Register new user (Sign Up as Provider)

con:parameter.con:name: files
con:parameter.con:description: Attachments, limited to 8 items, max 2 MB each (array of files)
